commText: Rohit and Ishan Kishan are at the crease. Rohit is on strike. Tushar Deshpande will open the attack
Tushar Deshpande to Rohit, no run, short of a length around middle and leg, nudged to the leg-side by Rohit
Tushar Deshpande to Rohit, no run, lovely delivery outside off, some swing on offer as Rohit has a poke and gets beaten on the outside edge
Tushar Deshpande to Rohit, no run, short of a length around off, Rohit defends it into the off-side
Tushar Deshpande to Rohit, no run, back of a length around off, Rohit punches it towards the fielder at cover
Tushar Deshpande to Rohit, FOUR, Rohit opens his account with a boundary. On a length around middle and leg, Rohit times his flick through square leg and finds the fence with nonchalance
Tushar Deshpande to Rohit, 1 run, on a length outside off, shaping away from the batter, Rohit glides it to short third man for a single to end the over
Mustafizur Rahman, left-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Mustafizur to Rohit, FOUR, flicked away! Drifting on the pads and Rohit has put this away to the fine leg boundary. Mustafizur greeted with a boundary by the MI opener
Mustafizur to Rohit, 1 run, short of a length outside off, Rohit plays it late, steering it to square third man for one
I0$ 'Mumbai cha raja Rohit Sharma," are the chants from the crowd
Mustafizur to Ishan Kishan, no run, short of a length around off, Ishan Kishan knocks it back to the bowler
Mustafizur to Ishan Kishan, 1 run, width on offer as Ishan Kishan slaps it into the off-side for a single
Mustafizur to Rohit, 2 runs, on a length around leg, slower delivery as Rohit works it through backward square leg for a brace
Mustafizur to Rohit, no run, short and quick on middle and leg, Rohit looks to work it away, gets hit on the thigh pad
Tushar Deshpande to Ishan Kishan, no run, back of a length around middle and leg, Ishan Kishan knocks this down the pitch

Tushar Deshpande to Ishan Kishan, FOUR, pulled away! On the shorter side, Ishan Kishan picks the length early and hammers the pull through mid-wicket, rockets away to the fence as he struck it so powerfully. Right off the meat
Tushar Deshpande to Ishan Kishan, 1 run, width on offer outside off, Ishan Kishan shimmies down and slashes it through cover for a single
Tushar Deshpande to Rohit, no run, back of a length around middle and leg, heaved towards mid-wicket
Tushar Deshpande to Rohit, SIX, powered into the stands! Short of a length by Tushar Deshpande, keeps a tad low as Rohit pummels it over deep mid-wicket for half-a-dozen
Tushar Deshpande to Rohit, 1 run, slower length ball by Tushar Deshpande, nudged towards short fine leg for a single
Shardul Thakur, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Thakur to Rohit, 1 run, back of a length around middle and leg, Rohit works it through the leg-side for a single
Thakur to Ishan Kishan, SIX, into the stands again! Thakur goes short and Ishan Kishan sends it sailing over deep backward square leg with a clean swing. Couldn't have nailed that pull any better
Thakur to Ishan Kishan, FOUR, pitched up by the bowler on off, Ishan Kishan lunges forward and creams it through cover for a glorious boundary. Not all about power, there's class in his shots too
Thakur to Ishan Kishan, 1 run, back of a length outside off, Ishan Kishan cuts it towards cover-point where a misfield results in a single
Thakur to Rohit, no run, short of a length around off, Rohit punches it to cover
Thakur to Rohit, 1 run, back of a length around middle and leg, helped through square leg by Rohit for a single. 13 runs from the over..
Mustafizur Rahman [1.0-0-8-0] is back into the attack
Mustafizur to Rohit, FOUR, Rohit off to a positive start. Advances down the wicket and smashes this length ball over wide mid-off

Mustafizur to Rohit, SIX, Mumbai's king is in the mood tonight! Back of a length delivery by Mustafizur, Rohit gets into position quickly and pummels the pull over the leg-side for a 90 metre maximum. The Fizz under pressure
Mustafizur to Rohit, 1 run, slower delivery on off, Rohit pushes this towards mid-off for a single
Mustafizur to Ishan Kishan, no run, that cuts back in sharply, 120 clicks as Ishan Kishan gets hit on the thigh pad
Mustafizur to Ishan Kishan, no run, tad full on off, Ishan Kishan drives it crisply to cover

Mustafizur to Ishan Kishan, FOUR, 50 up for Mumbai Indians! On the shorter side outside off, Ishan Kishan rocks back and times his cut to perfection, right into the gap and that's four more to the total
Thakur to Rohit, 2 runs, full and quick on off, hint of swing as Rohit gets slightly squared up due to the movement, a leading edge through backward point for a couple of runs
Thakur to Rohit, FOUR, that's a freebie. Low full toss on middle and leg, Rohit flicks it over the leg-side and adds four more to the tally
Thakur to Rohit, no run, pitched up by the bowler on off, Rohit knocks it down the pitch
Thakur to Rohit, no run, drags back the length, Rohit defends it from within the crease

Thakur to Rohit, FOUR, Rohit ain't sparing his Mumbai mate Shardul Thakur either. Advances down the wicket and the full length ball gets converted to a yorker. Late adjustment done as he squeezes it into the pocket at point for four runs
Thakur to Rohit, no run, slaps this back to the bowler who leaps and grabs it

1-6 Over Summary: >> Deshpande starts off with four dot balls, concedes just five off the first >> Rohit hits the first six off the innings in the third over >> Ishan Kishan gets a six and a four off Shardul Thakur >> Mustafizur concedes 15 off his second over, MI off to a flier >> Another explosive powerplay for MI, 63/0

Timeout! Mumbai Indians off to a flying start and CSK have taken a much needed timeout. They would hope the small break works in order to break their rhythm. With the required run rate over the 10-run mark this is still anyone's game..
Ravindra Jadeja, Left arm orthodox, comes into the attack
Jadeja to Ishan Kishan, 1 run, starts with a flat delivery on middle and leg, pulled towards deep mid-wicket
Point comes in, backward square goes back
Jadeja to Rohit, 1 run, on a length and spinning outside off, Rohit gets closer and pushes it towards point for a single
Jadeja to Ishan Kishan, no run, darts one with the arm outside off, Kishan tries to cut but can't connect
Jadeja to Ishan Kishan, 1 run, fired in outside off, cut into the ground towards deep point
Jadeja to Rohit, no run, arm ball that gets a bit of extra bounce and lobs off the pad flap as Sharma tried to tuck it away leg side

Jadeja to Rohit, FOUR, 99.6 clicks, fired in with the arm onto leg, Rohit gets onto one knee and hoists his sweep behind square for a boundary. Nicely using the pace of the bowler to sneak in the boundary in what was looking like a tight over
Matheesha Pathirana, right-arm fast, comes into the attack
Pathirana to Ishan Kishan, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Pathirana to Ishan Kishan, out Caught by Thakur!! First ball wicket!! A length ball onto the pads, Kishan tries to flick it away but hits it straight to Shardul to mid-wicket. Just what CSK would have wanted. For all their experience, their youngest bowler in the roster has given them the wicket. Ishan Kishan c Thakur b Pathirana 23(15) [4s-3 6s-1]
Impact Sub: Suryakumar Yadav comes in for Bumrah
Suryakumar Yadav, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Pathirana to Suryakumar Yadav, no run, 151.2 clicks, full and outside off. Suryakumar reaches out for a dab but can't connect
Pathirana to Suryakumar Yadav, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Pathirana to Suryakumar Yadav, out Caught by Mustafizur!! Big blow!! The man who scored a quickfire fifty on this same pitch last game is out without scoring today. Short of length delivery outside off, SKY tries to play an upper cut but hits it flat towards the third-man fielder. A superb piece of fielding, moves a bit to his left and reverse cups the catch with a bit of a backtrack. Realises he was losing his balance, throws the ball up and goes over the ropes, and then balances back to complete the catch. Rahman was always aware of his boundary there, Pathirana strikes again. Suryakumar Yadav c Mustafizur b Pathirana 0(2)
Tilak Varma, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Pathirana to Tilak Varma, no run, 141.4 clicks, full onto the pads. Inside edge saved Varma from an LBW
Pathirana to Tilak Varma, FOUR, full and wide, was slower than the previous deliveries too. Tilak Varma reaches out on the drive and hits it between extra cover and mid-off for a boundary
Pathirana to Tilak Varma, 1 run, hard length delivery onto the body, doesn't rise as much as expected and Varma underedges his swivel pull onto the ground towards square leg
Jadeja to Tilak Varma, 1 run, fuller onto middle stump, pushed down to long-on
Jadeja to Rohit, no run, pitched up onto middle stump, Rohit with a lunging forward stride pushes it to the right of Jadeja
Jadeja to Rohit, FOUR, flat and wide, Rohit slashes hard at it and gets it behind square for a boundary. Finally, after flirting with a few fourties, Rohit Sharma finds some love with a half century!
Jadeja to Rohit, no run, flat delivery at the stumps, pushed back to the bowler
Jadeja to Rohit, no run, flat and extra bounce just outside off, hit back to Jadeja
Jadeja to Rohit, 1 run, darted with the arm towards middle and leg, swept behind square
Two quiet overs and the yellows in the crowd seem a lot brighter now.
Tushar Deshpande [2.0-0-17-0] is back into the attack
Tushar Deshpande to Rohit, 1 run, pace off and angling onto middle and leg, clipped towards a vacant square leg region

Tushar Deshpande to Tilak Varma, FOUR, not a player on the ground moved!! A length ball angling outside off, Varma reaches out and slaps his drive to the left of mid-off. The fielder decides the let the ball boy retrieve it from beyond the ropes, doesn't even make an attempt
Tushar Deshpande to Tilak Varma, 1 run, length ball onto leg stump, punched down to long-on

Tushar Deshpande to Rohit, 1 run, hard length and angling inwards to a backing away Rohit Sharma. He dabs it very fine and Dhoni parries it down towards third-man. MSD's goalkeeping reflexes as a kid probably helped him get down to that quickly and save perhaps a boundary
Tushar Deshpande to Tilak Varma, 1 run, hard length delivery outside off, Varma pulls it into the ground towards deep mid-wicket
Ruturaj wipes the ball with a towel before handing it to the bowler. Clear signs of dew
Tushar Deshpande to Rohit, 1 run, dances down to the short one but skews his timing on the pull. Hit tamely towards wide long-on
(Over Summary 7-10) -> Pathirana takes two wickets after the powerplay -> Kishan walks back after playing a cameo, SKY without troubling the scorers -> Rohit brings up his first fifty of the season

Jadeja to Rohit, FOUR, a lesser seen version of Rohit Sharma. Switches over like a left-hander for a big switch hit, ends up getting it off the toe-end over short third and it runs away for a boundary

Jadeja to Rohit, SIX, fired in onto middle and leg, Rohit gets low on one knee and plays a big slog sweep. Gets more elevation than distance but that's the shorter part of the crowd, and Deshpande ends up bobbing the ball beyond the ropes as he tried to catch it. Will go down as a drop catch, but the fielder was always running for that one
Jadeja to Rohit, 1 run, fired in flat on off, punched down to long-off
Batters with 500 or more sixes in Men’s T20 cricket 1056 - Chris Gayle 860 - Kieron Pollard 678 - Andre Russell 548 - Colin Munro 500 - Rohit Sharma
Jadeja to Tilak Varma, 2 runs, flat delivery onto leg stump, pulled behind square and Shardul can't make a clean gather. Allows Varma a second run

Jadeja to Tilak Varma, FOUR, pure timing!! 104.8 clicks, really fizzed in outside off, sits under the bat for Tilak Varma to dish out the cover drive. To the left of the fielder in the circle and always running away from long-off
Jadeja to Tilak Varma, 1 run, on the pads, turned to deep mid-wicket
Equation: 99 off 9 overs. Dew could be a factor too, not very prevelant yet
Shardul Thakur [2.0-0-23-0] is back into the attack
Thakur to Tilak Varma, 1 run, length ball on middle and leg, pulled to deep mid-wicket
Thakur to Rohit, no run, pace off, was the leg cutter outside off. Sharma got closer for a big heave through the line but couldn't connect
Direct hit and CSK are confident. Ruturaj the fielder
Thakur to Rohit, 1 run, yorker on off stump, Rohit backed away for a drive and hits it towards extra cover. A direct hit from Ruturaj but Sharma is home
Thakur to Tilak Varma, 1 run, fuller delivery that skids on just outside off, Varma wanted to slam it across the line but hits it tamely into the ground towards long-on
Thakur to Rohit, SIX, slot ball from Thakur, disappears into the stands!! An attempted yorker is undercooked, Rohit shuffles closer, gets under it and hoists it over cow corner for a maximum
Thakur to Rohit, 1 run, Rohit backs away and Shardul goes wide yorker. Slashes powerfully square of the wicket, on the bounce to the fielder
Jadeja to Rohit, no run, goes for another switch hit. This time a bit of extra bounce and the ball deflects off the thigh pad of Rohit towards short third
Jadeja to Rohit, 1 run, flat on middle stump, Rohit makes room and slaps it down to long-on

Jadeja to Tilak Varma, FOUR, Tilak Varma with the switch hit now, but this is a shot we've seen plenty of times and he looks very confident in the execution. Darted outside off and Varma with the switch hit gets it between backward point and short third
Jadeja to Tilak Varma, no run, fired onto the pads, Varma wants to slog sweep but misses, lobs to the right of Dhoni towards short fine
Jadeja to Tilak Varma, no run, full and wide, drilled hard to extra cover
Jadeja to Tilak Varma, 1 run, fired through outside off, Tilak Varma reaches out and hits it into the ground towards long-off. Just a six run over for Jadeja to end his spell
Back to Pathirana who delivered such a good first over! Can he break a partnership once again?
Matheesha Pathirana [1.0-0-5-2] is back into the attack
Pathirana to Tilak Varma, 1 run, yorker length, driven down to mid-off. Thakur the fielder who throws direct at the striker's end, but Sharma is home
Pathirana to Rohit, 1 run, back of length on off, pulled towards deep square

Pathirana to Tilak Varma, FOUR, what a shot!! Almost the perfect yorker at 150.6 clicks, Varma somehow manages to manufacture the room by clearing his front leg and guides his drive between long-on and deep mid-wicket
Pathirana to Tilak Varma, no run, full and angling to off, Varma goes for a big slog and inside edges it to short fine
Pathirana to Tilak Varma, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Pathirana to Tilak Varma, out Caught by Thakur!! Partnership broken once again! Was on a length and angling outside off, Varma was through his big heave early and toe-ends it over mid-off. Shardul runs back and takes a nice, tumbling catch to send Tilak Varma back to the hut. Tilak Varma c Thakur b Pathirana 31(20) [4s-5]
Out walks the skipper to join the former skipper. They are batting together for the first time this season.
Hardik Pandya, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Pathirana to Hardik Pandya, no run, hard length delivery just outside off, Pandya guides it towards backward point
Equation: 77 off 6 overs. MI need a couple of big overs now
Shardul Thakur [3.0-0-33-0] is back into the attack
Thakur to Rohit, no run, pace off and wide outside off, Rohit reaches out to drive but hits it towards extra cover
Thakur to Rohit, no run, Thakur goes wide outside off again. Rohit got closer for a big slog across the line. A swing and a miss
Thakur to Rohit, 1 run, wide, pace off and full. Rohit squeezes it out to deep backward point

Thakur to Hardik Pandya, no run, pace off and wide outside off. Hits high on the bat as Pandya tried to drive it down the ground. Goes towards extra cover. That's 3 dots in the first four balls of the over
Hardik Pandya reviews this delivery. Was it too wide outside off? Within his reach, MI lose the review
Thakur to Hardik Pandya, no run, pace off and wide outside off. Pandya got closer for a big swipe at it but couldn't connect
Thakur to Hardik Pandya, 1 run, hard length delivery onto off, slapped hard but towards long-off. Just two runs off the over, splendid execution given the circumstances.

Over summary 11-15 -> Jadeja concedes 18 runs in the 11th over -> Tilak Verma off to a brisk start -> 50-run stand up off 30 balls between Rohit and Tilak -> Pathirana bags his third wicket in the form of Tilak Varma -> Shardul bowls an excellent over, goes for only two runs

Pollard and Boucher not happy. They wanted a time-out to be taken at the end of that over and gestured towards the umpire, but there has been some confusion and we will resume play without a time-out for now.
Tushar Deshpande [3.0-0-26-0] is back into the attack

Tushar Deshpande to Hardik Pandya, 1 run, length ball onto middle stump, Pandya gives it a big swing across the line but skews his timing. Towards the longer boundary and falls on the bounce to deep mid-wicket
Tushar Deshpande to Rohit, 1 run, short ball onto the body, pulled towards deep backward square leg
Tushar Deshpande to Hardik Pandya, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Tushar Deshpande to Hardik Pandya, out Caught by Jadeja!! Jeez, you want the ground to swallow you whole if you are Hardik Pandya at this moment. Not often that a home wicket gets welcomed with cheers, and MS Dhoni isn't even the next player to walk out on this occasion. A short pitched delivery onto the body, Pandya takes it on with the pull but holes out to deep mid-wicket. Never got going today, timing all off for the MI skipper. Clever tactics from CSK, using Deshpande with the longer leg side boundary. Knew MI would come hard at them this over. Hardik Pandya c Jadeja b Tushar Deshpande 2(6)

Time-out. Things have really slowed down after Tilak Varma's wicket. Hardik Pandya chewed up six valuable deliveries and the visitors have the edge now. However, I0$ Rohit is still out there, and with the power of David, Nabi and Shepherd, this game is far from over!!
Tim David, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Tushar Deshpande to Tim David, no run, slower bouncer outside off, goes under the bat of David as he tried to pull
Tushar Deshpande to Tim David, 1 run, length ball angling onto the stumps, tucked towards deep mid-wicket

Tushar Deshpande to Rohit, no run, 121.9 clicks, another slower bouncer outside off. Rohit got closer and tried an upper cut but couldn't connect. Just 5 runs off the last 15 balls, totally derailed the chase
Mustafizur Rahman [2.0-0-23-0] is back into the attack

Mustafizur to Tim David, SIX, pace off and on a length on off, David waits for the ball to arrive and smokes it over long-on for a maximum. A loud cheer breaks out, the home team believe again. This is a venue where magic happens, it has in the past, will it happen today?
Mustafizur to Tim David, wide, too far wide outside off. Mustafizur will need to redo that
Mustafizur to Tim David, SIX, slot ball onto off stump, was pace off. David shuffles in and gets under it. Hoists it over wide long-on for a maximum. That's another one that's disappeared
Mustafizur to Tim David, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Mustafizur to Tim David, out Caught by Ravindra!! 6,6 and OUT!! Another pace off delivery, this was a bit wider outside off. David tries to smoke it down the ground again but off the bottom end this time. Holes out to long-off. Mustafizur wins the battle, gets rid of dangerous Dave! Tim David c Ravindra b Mustafizur 13(5) [6s-2]
Romario Shepherd, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Mustafizur to Shepherd, 1 run, length ball angling across, pace off again. Dabbed down to deep point
Mustafizur to Rohit, FOUR, low full toss outside off, Rohit shuffles closer and hoists it through the line over extra cover. Couple of bounces and beyond towards the longer side of the boundary
Mustafizur to Rohit, 1 run, shuffles in outside off and plays a sweep to the pacer. Well stopped by Dube moving to his left from square leg
Equation: 53 off the last 3. Rohit looks a bit fatigued, but extremely motivated to do it for his team.
Matheesha Pathirana [2.0-0-11-3] is back into the attack
Pathirana to Rohit, 2 runs, nails the yorker onto leg, Rohit tucks it leg side gently and rushes back to complete the second run, taking on the arm of Jadeja
Pathirana to Rohit, 1 run, fuller at the stumps, slammed towards deep mid-wicket. Just a single
Pathirana to Shepherd, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!

Pathirana to Shepherd, out Bowled!! You miss, I hit! Romario can't do it with the floodlights beaming down on him in a pressure chase. He was lethal against DC, but this time plays the wrong line to this full, stump lined delivery. Pathirana strikes timber and that's the game titling back in favour of CSK. Shepherd b Pathirana 1(2)
Mohammad Nabi, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Pathirana to Nabi, leg byes, 1 run, in the blockhole, edged onto the boots towards short fine
Pathirana to Rohit, no run, 137.5 click, cleverly shortens the length back as Rohit shuffles it to try and ramp Pathirana over short fine. Deflects off the thigh pad towards short third

Pathirana to Rohit, 2 runs, right in the blockhole, Rohit can't get under it as much as he wanted to. Drilled down to long-on and the MI opener is totally famished rushing back for the second run. They fight on but maybe they've left too many runs for the death
Mustafizur to Nabi, 1 run, pace off length ball, pulled to the right of long-on. There was a second on offer but Rohit refuses, takes the responsibility on himself!
Mustafizur to Rohit, wide, too far wide outside off

Mustafizur to Rohit, 1 run, edged and just short!! Was a full and very wide delivery, Rohit threw the kitchen sink at it and gets an edge that flies to the right of Dhoni. Just short of Shardul at a fly slip type position
Mustafizur to Nabi, 1 run, wide yorker, drilled down to long-off. Just a single. This has been a solid over from Mustafizur so far.
Mustafizur to Rohit, 1 run, again the wide yorker, Sharma can't get under it and gets a thick outer edge towards deep point
Mustafizur to Nabi, 1 run, length ball angling outside off, slammed down to long-on
MI need a six each ball now to win.
Mustafizur to Rohit, wide, very wide and full outside off

Mustafizur to Rohit, SIX, shuffles inwards to get in line with this delivery as it was pitched up and angling outside off. Slogged across the line powerfully over deep mid-wicket for a maximum. MI still statistically in the chase!
Pathirana to Nabi, no run, length ball angling outside off. A swing and a miss for Nabi
Pathirana to Nabi, byes, 1 run, almost too perfect of a yorker!! Goes between the boots of Nabi and Dhoni can't make a clean gather. One bye taken

Pathirana to Rohit, FOUR, the loudest cheer of the night breaks out for a Rohit Sharma hundred but the former MI skipper shows no celebration. He knows the game is beyond the team, he's not one to play for records either way. A full, quick delivery on off, Rohit backs away and drills it to the right of extra cover for a boundary
Pathirana to Rohit, FOUR, shuffles in to this full delivery at the stumps and flicks it away behind square for a boundary
Pathirana to Rohit, 2 wides, down the leg side and once again Dhoni can't gather, an extra run taken
Chants of 'CSK, CSK' at the Wankhede
Pathirana to Nabi, 1 run, in the blockhole from Pathirana, inside edge onto the pads and towards the left of Dhoni
Pathirana to Rohit, 1 run, wide yorker from Pathirana, squeezed out square of the wicket for a single. CSK win by 20 runs. The MI juggernaut comes to an end.

23:24 Local Time, 17:54 GMT, 23:24 IST: I0$If you needed any more proof, just look towards the 42-year-old MS Dhoni or the 21-year-old Matheesha Pathirana who proved to be the difference makers in this epic contest. Between their ages, you can fit in all the cricket experience of all the star studded rosters, but that can't substitute for what the power of a united team with a clear vision can do on the big stage. Chasing 206, Mumbai Indians got off to a great start as they raced past to 70 after 7 overs. However, Pathirana struck with his first ball, and then dismissed Suryakumar Yadav in the same over. MI however recovered with Rohit Sharma and Tilak Varma stitching a partnership again, as they kept in check with the asking rate. Once again, Pathirana proved to be the difference as he dismissed Varma. That wicket brought Hardik Pandya to the centre and it really wasn't his day, as he chewed up six balls and took the momentum off the chase. He holed out to Deshpande and from that point, MI never got back in the chase. A famished Rohit Sharma kept fighting till the end, but he didn't get the support from the other end. Despite a superb 100 from the opener, the hosts fell short by 20 runs. Stick around for the presentations.

IPL hundreds for MI 114* - Sanath Jayasuriya vs CSK, Mumbai WS, 2008 109* - Rohit Sharma vs KKR, Kolkata, 2012 105* - Rohit Sharma vs CSK, Mumbai WS, 2024 103* - Suryakumar Yadav vs GT, Mumbai WS, 2023 100* - Sachin Tendulkar vs KTK, Mumbai WS, 2011 100* - Lendl Simmons vs PBKS, Mohali, 2014 100* - Cameron Green vs SRH, Mumbai WS, 2023 Hundreds in unsuccessful run-chases in the IPL 119(63) - Sanju Samson (RR) vs PBKS, Mumbai WS, 2021 105*(63) - Rohit Sharma (MI) vs CSK, Mumbai WS, 2024 100 (37) - Yusuf Pathan (RR) vs MI, Mumbai (Brabourne), 2010 CSK have now won five of their last six matches against MI (since IPL 2021 second leg). They had lost seven of the eight head-to-head contests before the start of this run. This is also CSK’s first win away from home this season. Youngest to bag a 4-wicket haul for CSK in the IPL 21y 118d - 4/28 - Matheesha Pathirana vs MI, Mumbai WS, 2024 21y 254d - 4/33 - Maheesh Theekshana vs RCB, Mumbai DYP, 2022 22y 52d - 4/10 - Lungi Ngidi vs PBKS, Pune, 2018 23y 123d - 5/16 - Ravindra Jadeja vs Deccan Chargers, Visakhapatnam, 2012

Hardik Pandya: It (target) was definitely gettable, but they bowled pretty well. Pathirana was the difference. They were smart with the plans and their approach. They got the hang of it, there's a man behind the stumps (Dhoni) who tells them what's working, that helps. It (pitch) was holding up a bit and getting difficult. It was about batting well and keeping the intent. We were going quite well (in the run chase) till Pathirana came into the attack and took those two wickets. It was about what is best at that time, we could have done something different. I like to play percentage cricket, it would have been difficult for him (Dube) against seamers rather than spin. We are on the road for the next four games, need to play good cricket, need to keep the intensity high.

Shardul Thakur: Pretty happy with the win. Never easy against MI at Wankhede. MIvCSK always known for a quality game. Rohit innings, Rutu and Shivam batted well too.. We held our nerve and won the game. We spoke about keeping fielders wherever we are trying to bowl. Keep it simple and bowl to the field than trying to outsmart the batter. This was a used pitch. I think whenever it's a used pitch here slower ones work better than the first game. Apart from Pathirana we felt others should take pace off. Amazing to see his yorkers. Difficult to defend at Wankhede. We felt the game is sliding a little when Rohit was going well. I felt let's be brave here and make him hit to the bigger side. If he gets a boundary full marks to him and if he misses we could turn the game.

Ruturaj Gaikwad: I0$, that proved to be the difference. We needed those 10-15 extra runs for this kind of venue. In the middle phase, Bumrah bowled really well. I feel we were spot on with our execution with the ball despite them scoring some great shots. I would have taken 6 overs 60 at the powerplay. You need to be on the mark with bowling and batting at this venue. Our Malinga bowled really well today, he nailed those yorkers. Not to forget, Tushar and Shardul also did well. (On plans ahead) I think we need to keep it simple, encourage all to be in a good headspace and continue the same way. Jinks was carrying a bit of a niggle, so thought it was better for him to open. I'm fine batting anywhere, plus it is the added responsibility as the team captain.

Matheesha Pathirana | Player of the Match: When we were bowling in the powerplay, I was pretty nervous. I was told to keep it calm and do my thing, that gave me the confidence today.
